**a.** Increase filter size (F). This expands receptive field allowing better capture long range dependencies between pixels while maintaining spatial resolution due  to grouped convolutions implementation. A common doubling strategy would involve increasing F from 'w’ filters into ‘W‘filters where W> w, keeping group convolution intact..   



