**a.** Reduce redundant layers:** The model has two consecutive linear-relu pairs followed  by a sigmoid activation layer which is commonly used for binary classification tasks. Instead, one could combine these into fewer convolutional blocks using techniques like squeeze -and expand architectures that leverage bottlenecks combined   with dilated convolutions.. This reduces both complexity as well number operations per unit volume (FLOPs).




 **b**. Use lower dimensional embedding spaces**: In general reducing dimensions leads reduction on memory footprint but might introduce information loss due overfitting if not implemented carefully,. Here we use `int` instead og float embeddings hoping it would significantly decrease computational cost alongside lowering dimensionality from ``Cin`` down To an integer multiple (`Int[ Cin / Ratio ]`) based off our downsampling factor "Ratio".





***c.*** Employ quantization Techniques-: Quantizing weights during training process drastically decreases their size thereby optimizing resource utilization Without significant dropoff performance metrics such mean squared error.(MSE.) However implementing quantized networks requires additional infrastructure changes hence should only considered after exploring other options first



These approaches collectively minimize unnecessary computations whilst preserving desired functionalities enabling efficient implementation within limited hardware resources

