### **Parameter Tuning**:





#### ***a.** Kernel Size (`Ks`) Adjustment:- Increasing kernel width expands receptive field thereby extracting more features from neighboring pixels at cost increased computational complexity.<br> For instance doubling kernels would double computation time but extract twice number feature maps compared vanilla implementation.(Note increasing k beyond certain limit leads diminishing returns due overfitting).<p/>






##### ****b**. Ceiling Mode Optimization :- Switching ceiling modes allows tailoring spatial dimensions according desired output shape while maintaining aspect ratio between inputs outputs enabling fine tuning network architecture without altering underlying image structure..(e g switching off ceilling introduces zero paddings effectively reducing effective filter widths ). <P />         ﻿​ ​  ‍⬛️‍♀️⁣~--~~ ~~|~~~ |__,,,_| \_\_\_\_\n&nbsp;&bull;(c.) Employ Batch Normalization After Convolutions-: Implementing batch normalization after convolution layers helps stabilize learning processes mitigating internal covariate shift issues arising recurrently across different channels improving overall robustness against adversarial attacks.` &emsp;-.;,;;,;;-;!;! ;:::::::::||----->>>>>\\r \t "This text describes modifications proposed based upon understanding provided" )# Please provide further details regarding each modification along side their anticipated impact if implemented successfully.​

